==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English [[shanke]], from Old English [[scanca]]

===Noun===
'''shank'''
# The lower part of the [[leg]]; [[shin]]
# A [[straight]], [[narrow]] part of an [[object]]; [[shaft]]; [[stem]]
# A [[protruding]] part of an object, by which it is or can be [[attached]]
# (slang) An improvised [[stabbing]] [[weapon]]
# {{sports}} A poorly played [[golf]] shot where the ball is struck by the part of the club head that connects to the shaft

====Derived terms====
* [[greenshank]]
* [[redshank]]

===Verb===
'''to shank'''
# (archaic) To [[travel]] on foot